textDelta: what were the results of the Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions? The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions (SORT) was an agreement to reduce strategic nuclear arms. It was signed by US President Ronald Reagan and Soviet General Secretary Mikhail Gorbachev on 8 December 1987. The treaty was ratified by the United States Senate on 25 June 1988 and came into force on 5 June 1991. The treaty required the two countries to eliminate their nuclear and conventional ground-launched ballistic and cruise missiles with ranges of between 500 and 5,500 kilometres (300 and 3,400 miles).
